                <div class="span8 marT30 col marT0small">
<h3>'Work in that unit? I won't do it.'</h3>
<p>The New Kru Town slum in Monrovia has no public water supply, no toilets, no sanitation system, no electricity. People live in hovels slapped together from wood and metal. Most people have no running water, other than what's in the streets when downpours soak the neighborhood.</p>
<p>Sometime in late May or early June, at least six people in New Kru Town came down with Ebola. There were wild rumors that someone had poisoned their food.</p>
<p>Brown received a call on the evening of June 11 from someone at the Liberian ministry of health who asked: Do you still have an Ebola unit? Yes, Brown said.</p>
