                <div class="intro-description panel-txt">In late 2013, the Ebola virus jumped from an unknown animal species to the human population. The outbreak's first victim may have been a 2-year-old girl from Guinea. Cases soon surfaced in the Guinean rain forest, near the country's borders with Sierra Leone and Liberia. From there, it spread throughout West Africa.</div>
