                                                    The glow from a crematorium fire lights up the night sky where bodies of people who died from Ebola are cremated on Sept. 14 in Monrovia. The crematorium was built by the Indian Embassy but has been transformed to cremate up to 120 people at a time to deal with the Ebola crisis.                                                                        </p>
