                    <h2 class="postitle">What is ZMapp?</h2>

                    <div class="single_metainfo">On October 6, 2014</div>

                    <div class="zn_post_wrap"><p>ZMapp is one of the most common experimental treatment for people who have been infected with Ebola virus. It has a three different monoclonal antibodies which bind to the protein of the Ebola virus. It has not been tested on human for its effectiveness and safety.</p>
<p>ZMapp has been used on monkeys where it prompted recovery in 18 macaque monkeys which had been infected with the virus. This drug has shown better results more so in monkeys. For instance, when this drug was administered to a money which had been infected five days after the infection (a point where Ebola is its advanced state) it did reversed bleeding, rashes and elevated liver enzymes that are Ebola‚Äôs hallmayürk symptoms. It also reduced the symptoms to insignificant levels. On the other hand, other monkeys which were not given the ZMapp died within 8 days.</p>
<p>Since this drug was manufactured, it had never been used on human beings until it was given to Brantly and Writebol in the last ditch to save their lives. But still, scientists cannot quantify the role this experimental drug played in their life during the recovery process. The experimental drug appeared promising and had been given to five other Ebola patients two of whom had died. CDC also made it clear that the manufacturer of ZMapp is still evaluating the effectiveness and safety of the drugs which had been distributed.</p>
<p>At the moment, CDC has insisted that the only way to know whether the drug is efficient is to conduct a randomized controlled clinical trial in people to compare the outcome of people who receive the treatment and the untreated patients. Up to date no such studies has been conducted.</p>
<p>CDC has made it clear that until now, there is no standard treatment for Ebola and all the health officers do is to provide supportive therapy. The supportive therapy includes the following key measures: balancing the patients&#8217; fluids and electrolytes; treating them for any complicating infections and maintaining their oxygen status and blood pressure.</p>
<p>They have insisted that best way to stop the current Ebola outbreak in West Africa is only by identifying those who have been infected, isolating them, tracing contacts to avoid chain transmission and adopting safe burial practices. This is how the previous Ebola outbreaks have been stopped.</p>
<p>Basically, ZMapp is not a vaccine, it is developed as a therapeutic treatment for people who have been infected with Ebola. Therapeutics are provided to people who have the virus already. This is not always the case for the vaccines which are administered to boost the immune system of the body before it gets exposed to the virus or bacteria. This immune system can therefore fight infection. ZMapp has been designed in such a way that when it is introduced in the body the monoclonal antibody binds to the virus so that the immune system of body can clear the existing Ebola virus in the body. There is no Ebola vaccine which has been clinically tested and approved. However, the NIH‚Äôs National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases is working on developing an Ebola vaccine.</p>
<p>This has been one of the largest Ebola virus disease outbreak and there could be a reason to hasten the clinical test of the existing experimental treatments. As a matter of fact, experimental treatments may not be 100% perfect since the manufacturers have to monitor their outcome and decide whether to manufacture more of it or make further adjustments to make more effective. This could take a little longer.</p>
<p>Canada has also produced the VSV-EBOV vaccine which they have donated. The NewLink Genetics has license rights through a wholly owned subsidiary BioProtection Systems which was to develop the product for human use. According to NewLink Genetics, clinical trials had been developed with experts from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration, the World Health Organization, U.S. National Institutes of Health the U.S. Department of Defence, the¬†Centers for Disease Control and the European counterparts.</p>
<p>According to Eve Adams, who is the parliamentary secretary for minister of health, they had donated 1,000 doses to the WHO and it is their responsibility mange all the logistics required and dispense efficiently.</p>
