			<p>You touched on something else that I want to address.  Despite what hit-piece TV shows try to portray, there really isn&#8217;t such a thing as &#8220;you preppers.&#8221;  Preppers are not a homogenous group.  &#8220;Preppers&#8221; span the gap from people who put extra gloves, food, and coats in their car in the winter in case they get stuck to people who buy abandoned missile silos to live in &#8220;just in case.&#8221;</p>
